Bobby Kotick

From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
  (Redirected from Robert Kotick)

					Jump to:					navigation, 					search






This article's lead section may not adequately summarize key points of its contents. Please consider expanding the lead to provide an accessible overview of all important aspects of the article. Please discuss this issue on the article's talk page. (July 2017)




Bobby Kotick



Robert Kotick



Born
(1963-03-01) March 1, 1963 (age 54)
United States


Alma mater
University of Michigan


Occupation
CEO of Activision Blizzard


Board member of
The Coca-Cola Company


Website
bobbykotick.org


Robert A. Kotick (born 1963)[1] is an American businessman[2] who serves as CEO of Activision Blizzard. On February 16, 2012, he was elected an outside director of The Coca-Cola Company.[2]
From 2003 until 2008, he was a director at Yahoo!.[2]



